i'm an ambient musician, sound engineer/producer and sound designer,  & photographer - currently based in Perth, Scotland, and i was also a full-time member of the global musical collective 48cameras, whose main base was in Belgium, which ended in 2019 after the death of its founder and leader Jean Marie Mathoul.

95% of the sounds i use and make are created using just the bass guitar as the main sound source. i rarely use synthesiser sounds, and all my recordings are done in the analogue domain, with 2 ESI400 hardware samplers at the heart of my recording set-up.

RED-EYE (Kris Giampa)
Combine House Music and Sound Design and you have created a passion for Producer / Remixer / Sound Designer RED-EYE.

His Big Room House productions and remixes have placed him among some of the most talented and skilled producers in the US, while consistently pushing the envelope for a unique and exciting sound. His ongoing pursuit for club pounding sexy House Music will bring the dance floors some very tired yet ecstatic bodies for years to come.
On the Video Game Sound Design side of things, he (Kris Giampa) is currently working at Blizzard Entertainment as a Senior Sound Designer on Diablo 3.

Antonio Kalem aka Tony Silver is born on 10.10.1984 in Sarajevo (Bosnia and Herzegowina). The first contact with electronic music he had was 1994, it was the year when he was listening to greatly popular Rave and Hardcore music. Thereby, year 1997 he decided to pursue his own production due to his huge interest in electronic music. At the first beginning he was working with Club and Hardcore music, but as he was experimenting with different styles â€“ he slowly moved to Hard Techno sounds, mostly inspired by Chris Liebing style of music whom he has been using as a substantial model in his production. He has been a long time into electronic music and his style can be defined simply as dark, aggressive, pounding techno, involving typical aggressive percussions. 
Today he and his friend Srle are running a Label "Ground Effect Records" which is based on harder and darker side of Techno. His own sets have considerable influence of dark atmosphere. In the present position he is working with new projects, productions as well as collaboration with artists such as Tuomas Rantanen and Dj Srle (as Hysteria).

DJs, producers, selectors â€” all these terms pertain to Round Table Knights, the eclectic, highly skilled duo of Biru Bee and Marc Hofweber, so why donâ€™t we just call them artists? Hailing from Switzerland, these warriors against the mundane have fought hard in the realm of house music to keep things fresh and support the new in their productions and DJ sets, as well as at their venue, Club Bonsoir. They present the tried and true anew while searching for the untested. 

Beginning with a taste in hip-hop, jazz, and electro, Biru and Marc have since paid their dues in the record bins and diversified their mixing palette even further. A deep knowledge spread across years and genres has brought them across the globe to respected venues and festivals such as Panorama Bar, SÃ³nar, Igloofest, and Creamfields. These crowd-whisperers mix for the body and the mind, deftly juxtaposing the cutting-edge and the classic, always locked in the groove. 

Meanwhile, their production style has been more or less refined to the realm of house, with a clear inflection of all those other styles they so love. Their tracks bump with an unpretentious experimentalism, devoid of obvious weirdness and bursting with musicality. Say What?!, their debut album released on Made To Play Records, set a high standard that theyâ€™ve been chipping away at with a number of killer singles and EPs dropped on an international range of discerning labels.

Even with such a broad base of experience, Round Table Knights remain wholly un-jaded and still have a long road to travel. Equipped with sharp ears, rich knowledge, and a distinctive catalogue of work, itâ€™s clear that theyâ€™ll always move forward and never lose the crowd along the way.

Ooit begonnen als zanger in een jeugdkoor, ruim 13 jaar lang. Het jeugdkoor werd ingeruild voor (lead)zang/gitaar/toetsen in bandjes. Na onder andere "Check Vamos & the Gonzo Coverband" kwam het acoustische duo "Cripple & the Blind", samen met Marc Smits, waarmee in de zomer van 2000 drie weken door Engeland en Noord-Ierland werd getourd. Covers - maar wel in een bijzonder creatieve jas. 
Met deze formatie is in de zomer van 2001 het lied "Ontbijt voor twee" geschreven ter gelegenheid van de introductie van nieuwe studenten in Wageningen. Voor die gelegenheid werd het duo tot quintet uitgebreid. Het duo heeft tot 2005 bestaan.

In 2001 begonnen met musical bij musicalvereniging Sempre Sereno, waarin onder andere opgevoerd Hair (Woof), Moulin Rouge (Christian), en the Rocky Horror Show (RiffRaff).
In de zomer van 2003 voor het openlucht-theaterstuk "Waar Wilde Wortels Wenken" van theatergroep Impuls muziek geschreven, samen met Yuri Stevens, en opgevoerd met een uitgebreide formatie. Werkte mee aan de danstheatervoorstelling "Driven by electricity" van danstheatergroep Pandance. Sinds 2005 zangles van Jimmy Hutchinson. De laatste jaren af en toe een solo performance als zanger/gitarist op diverse gelegenheden.

Danny Benedettini Items & Things One could say Danny Benedettini is inspired by punk-rock music and cult horror film icon, Lloyd Kaufman, but if you asked him what truly fuels his creative energy, his reply would be: ordinary life. While some try to decipher the real versus the unreal and the scary versus the funny, Benedettini sits back in the darkness and observes life quietly. Raised in the tiny Italian seaside town of Cervia, Benedettiniâ€šÃ„Ã´s teenage years were spent kicking it at a local punk-rock concert venue that first whetted his appetite for music production and an acoustic drum-set. With a sleep-deprived father under the same roof however, the drum-set was short-lived but Benedettiniâ€šÃ„Ã´s musical aspirations lingered on. His first introduction to minimal sound dates back to 2004 in New York City when a friend slipped him a Run Stop Restore CD. Benedettiniâ€šÃ„Ã´s fascination with the style grew bigger, his determination grew stronger and his connection grew closer as he sent demo after demo solely to Minus and later down the line, to Items & Things. In 2010 he released â€šÃ„ÃºScared of Boomâ€šÃ„Ã¹ on buddy label, Memento Records and after Magda and Troy Pierce adopted the tracks in their club sets, Benedettini crossed over to the receiving end of Items & Things in 2011 with his first EP release, "Tell Me Quietlyâ€šÃ„Ã¹. As a newbie in the field, he has swiftly accelerated with a fine ear for music and a versatile style ranging from disco tech house and dark disco of the 80s, to new wave and minimal. Benedettini keeps his vintage beats fresh and current with Ableton and Logic software utilizing synthesizers, drums and electric bass as well as other instuments. With Miami Winter Music Conference, Fabric, Rex Club and Nuits Sonores pumping on the tour circuit plus upcoming releases steaming in the pot, Benedettini is charging the electronic music waters with grace and speed. Lars Schneemann earlier known as DJ Snow, born and raised 1977 in Berlin. After certain time it pulled he into the town Wiesbaden, where he lives today. He created his own style of dj mixing and began playing 1993. His sound is FIDGET HOUSE and ELECTRO. The earliest inspirations came from DJ..s, like Antoine Clamaran, Laurent Wolf, Fred Pellechiro, Danny Marquez, DJ Fist, Carl Cox and many more... Exactly these sound was the reason why Lars Schneemann was decaying in electronic music. After collecting a lot of records it was his dream to work for a record label and to be a member of the music scene. With his reputation and knowledge of electronic music he acquired a position at Germany..s House Label Chicaria Records. From this point on he learned a lot about the music scene and with all his efforts he planned to keep the electronic music alive which gave him the earliest inspirations. In 2001, for the first time even he began to produce own Tracks and delivered Remixe for Dervish, Inaya Day, Lissat & Voltaxx, Jaimie Fanatic, Erick Decks, Groovedust, Streamrocker, Roman Pushkin and many more... SOIL & "PIMP" SESSIONS is an explosive Japanese jazz band, comprised of six musicians; Shacho (agitator, spirit), Tabu zombie (trumpet), Motoharu (sax), Josei (piano), Akita Goldman (bass) and Midorin (drums).

At its core, the group is about giving pulsating live performances. SOIL & "PIMP" SESSIONS combine the highest musicianship with the coolest of cool sounds and atmosphere. Their brand of jazz is rough around the edges, unadulterated entertainment and constantly kept at boiling point.

Each member brings his own unique talent and perspective. They originally met at a club event in Tokyo in 2001. The Tokyo club scene was dominated by DJs until SOIL & "PIMP" SESSIONS arrived, breaking the mold as live pioneers. Calling their music "DEATH JAZZ", they gained recognition for performing an original form of aggressive alternative jazz. The band comments; "We always felt that in the world of jazz, there was an unwritten rule that the musicians were to concentrate on their techniques and the audience were simply there to admire, like a transmitter/ receiver relationship. We wanted to break away from that and create exciting jazz with far more interaction between the players and the audience". Shacho, who holds a rather unusual title in a jazz band as "the agitator", plays a key role in this by stirring and stimulating the audience.

It did not take long for SOIL & "PIMP" SESSIONS to become one of the hottest new bands in Japan and becoming favorites of major festivals including Fuji Rock. Their international breakthrough came when Gilles Peterson, the renowned British DJ, introduced the them through his Radio 1 show "WorldWide". In the summer of 2005, by invitation from Giles, the band traveled to the UK to perform on his program. The name spread further via the international jazz network and at the BBC World Wide Award later that year, SOIL & "PIMP" SESSIONS was awarded with the "John Peel Play More Jazz Award".

While continuing to perform in Japan, the band expanded their playing field performing in over 12 European countries and at major international festivals including Montreux and North Sea.

The band's album 'Pimp Master' was released in 2006 through Compost in Europe and Brownswood Recordings in the UK. 'PIMPOINT' is scheduled for early summer release in Europe and the UK by Brownswood Recordings.

Miguel Bastidaâ€™s (1984, Granada, Spain) career has been steadily going up since he started DJing with only 14 years old, in the local radio station of his hometown, Alhama de Granada.
Nowadays living in Barcelona, Miguel has become one of the most in-demand Spanish artists worldwide, due to his versatility, great musical selection and charisma dominating the dancefloor.

Miguelâ€™s influences initially came from bands as The Prodigy or The Chemical Brothers, and also from harder styles, like hardtechno and breakbeats. Besides, he had one of South Spainâ€™s electronic music strongholds close to home: Industrial Copera. There, DJs as Ben Sims or Cristian Varela left a huge impression on Bastida, who also looked up to artists such as Nathan Fake, James Holden or Alex Under, during the golden years of minimal techno.

Miguel already dominated the mixing craft when he turned 16. After his first nights out, the idea of music production started to come to his mind. Picturing sounds with each song he listened to, Bastida started gathering with friends with the same ideas and taste for music, setting up his first live sets, which finally led to the foundation of his first group: the electronic music band RaÃ­z ElectrÃ³nica (Electronic Roots). After that, and thanks to his self-taught practice, he managed to dominate his first production software, Reason, changing to Logic afterwards. Today, being his weapon of choice when creating beats. His love for machines is also well known, especially for Moogâ€™s creations and MIDI controllers.

With his family support as mainstay, helping at the familyâ€™s business in the morning and focusing on the studio sessions during the afternoon, Miguel was able to dedicate himself to his great passion: the creation of tunes. Music production has been, without a question, what has taken Miguel Bastida where he is today. After years and years of being locked up in the studio, he managed to create his own, exclusive and uncompromised sound, whose turning point came in 2015, with the release of â€˜Moudnessâ€™, a track that managed to stay up in the Top charts of platforms such as Beatport. Before that, he already managed to knock on the doors of heavyweights as Umek and his 1605 platform. Then SÃ©bastien Legerâ€™s Mistakes Music came, followed by Mark Knightâ€™s Toolroom; Deeperfect; Trapez, elrow Music; Marc Marzenitâ€™s Paradigma Music; Dubfireâ€™s Sci-Tec; and most recently, Suara, demonstrating all the styles he dominates. Today his productions can be found in the selections of artists such as Richie Hawtin, Paco Osuna, Luciano, John Acquaviva or Leger, Dubfire or Umek themselves.

As DJ, Miguel Bastida belongs to the exclusive group of Spanish DJs that has had the chance of touring around the world, presenting his repertoire in almost every country in the planet, from Australia and New Zealand to electronic music strongholds as New York and Chicago. His name can also be found on the line-ups of the worldâ€™s best clubs and festivals, managing to convince even the most demanding dancefloors of the scene.

Self-taught and entrepreneur, Bastidaâ€™s projects ended up naturally in the creation of his own label, Be One Records, that he manages along two of his childhood friends. Bastida is in charge of the A&R, while his buddies in Berlin and Granada manage design and social networks duties. Recently they created a sub-label, dedicated to support and give a chance to young and upcoming talents of the electronic music scene.

Exactly 100 years after Albert Einstein, Markus G. is born in MuÌˆnster, Germany. As home of the legendary techno and house locations Cosmic Club and Dockland, MuÌˆnster becomes the western capital of the German electronic music movement in the 1990ies. At the age of 14, Markus discovers the Elevator, the first techno record shop of the region which strictly serves DJs, and starts jobbing there. Quickly he recognized his purpose and MGâ€™s mixing skills develop fast and his preference for a dark and straight-forward style of techno emerges with it. MGness is derived from selection of music that he becomes known for: â€œMarkus Gxxxxxrâ€™s Nervous Exciting Sound Spectrumâ€. 1995 The Cosmic Club gets awarded as Club of the Year by the Raveline Magazine. During this peak of the techno movement in MuÌˆnster, MGness designated as resident DJ into it.
He sets up his first proper sound studio directly above the main floor of the new Cosmic Club. Playing uncountable sets right before or after DJ icons like Sven VaÌˆth, Paul van Dyk, WestBam, Chris Liebing , Thomas Schumacher, Dave Angel or Luke Slater only feeds Markusâ€™ addiction to perfection as DJ and producer even more.
With his first appearance as main live act of a Cosmic Club night, a dream comes true for the elec- tronic musician MGness in 1999. In 2002 MGness releases his first EP called â€œRe-EPâ€ on Rawcanine Records, which is produced together with Kai Niggemann and Oliver Froning (Dune). As well in this Year the Raveline Magazine sends him as a DJ Instructor over to Ibiza for teaching the Art of DJing to Offspring DJs. When the Cosmic Club becomes homeless in 2003, MGness focuses on DJ gigs in clubs throughout Europe where he represents his musical home base.
End of 2004, MGness has the honor to produce the official anthem for Mysticland 15, the last event of the Cosmic Club makers. He performs it in his live act at primetime of this memorable final Cos- mic excess. His biggest release so far is â€œElevator DJ Tunesâ€, a 2-CD compilation which is sold World-wide. The compilation includes as well as 2 exclusive productions by Markus. Looking for a new challenge he moves to Frankfurt he gets a residency at the DC Funkfurt clubbing event series by 2008. Getting deeper and deeper into production technology, MGness releases the well-received â€œDreiundzwanzig EPâ€ on October 23, 2009. While MGness is busy in 2011 doing remixes for different artists, he has projected in 2012 new own Releases.

The criminally underrated Contepella is a DJ and producer who has been an active member of the bustling Oslo club scene since the late 90`s, when he joined the dj-collectives Skadubski Dj Team and later the Elektromonika crew. Both parties being busy making their mark by pushing more underground sounds like d&b, breaks and dubstep since its early beginnings.

A native of Italian island Sardinia, Alberto Andreoni first picked up a guitar at age 13, intitially lured by the glamour of rock music, but soon delved deeper into theory and classical guitar. By his late teens, Andreoni had already gained an international perspective (having called Denver, Rome and London his home) and decided to study formally at Berklee College of Music in Boston, spending his free time performing in combos at local cafes and lounges. By this point Andreoni was a bona fide jazz snob, but in 2000, upon relocating to New York City, he was ready to expand his musical frontiers. After a friend invited him to check out some of this precarious â€œtechnoâ€ music from a visiting Italian DJ (Marco Carola), Alberto was completely blown away, and his foray into electronic music production began.

In 2004, Alberto made yet another move, this time to Berlin where he found a fresh playground for his MIDI-guitar jams, creating live improvised dance music. In 2006, Signor Andreoniâ€™s first solo releases were released on on TuningSpork Records â€“ the Blues Experiment 12â€ series, which birthed five installments â€“ and the techno world capital proved to be fertile grounds for collaboration as well, leading to work with Samim, Jay Haze and Touane, as well as Renato, with whom he created a remix for Motorcitysoul on Lo-Fi Stereo.

Currently, Andreoni resides in Cagliari, Italy, where he co-runs T-Bet Records and focuses on two newer music projects: Bunkers (with releases on TuningSpork, Amam and Suara) together with Alessio Mereu, and Diamond Dog (Contexterrior, Tenax, T-Bet) in collaboration with Acirne. Tracks from both duos have been charted and heavily played by DJ heavyweights like Richie Hawtin and Adam Beyer, and electronic music authority Resident Advisor has praised Andreoniâ€™s productions as â€œambitiousâ€ and â€œskillfulâ€. Whether live on stage or â€œlive in the studioâ€ (the kind of approach any performer has toward production), whether with a guitar or computer, our nomadic protagonist shows no sign of retiring his craft, continuing to explore the interaction of traditional and modern music techniques.

ATOM is Matt Inconiglios. Heâ€™s been experimenting with sound ever since he re-wired his AM radio to play through an old guitar amplifier as a child. Excited by the possibilities of sound manipulation through electronics, ATOM now mixes music, sounds, dialogue, and whatever else he can find to create a surreal sonic painting, steeped in electronic beats.

Inspired by the works of The Orb, Akufen, Meat Beat Manifesto, Josh Wink, and Luke Vibert, ATOM creates mixes and original tracks using elements of the entire sound spectrum, ranging from classical music, to electronic beats, to found sounds of everyday life. Growing up DJing at all types of parties, events, and clubs, ATOM sharpened his skills of dance music mixing, constantly interjecting elements of surprise. Turntables, samplers, computers - ATOM now harnesses whatever gear he needs to take listeners on an impressive, and oddly hallucinogenic journey. Having rocked parties for over 25 years, ATOMâ€™s live DJ sets are always an audio delight.

Whether its a chorus of crickets from a backyard, two notes of a blues harmonica player, or a funked-out 1980s electro beatbox loop, ATOM will take sound samples from any source and morph them together to get his point across. Heâ€™s also been known to perform under the aliases of â€˜Precious Royâ€™, â€˜Arthur Pfundâ€™, and â€˜Matt Incâ€™.

Dave's first gig was at Lakota in Bristol UK in 1998. After a few years cutting his teeth in the student club scene plus a year in Germany in 2002 he won Muzik magazine's prestigious competition Bedroom Bedlam, completed his law degree and moved to Japan. During the 8 years he spent based in Tokyo he held regular residencies or events at Yellow (now Eleven), Womb, Warehouse702 and more injecting a dose of the UK/euro underground into the big-name dominated scene. At the same time as holding a lengthy residency for Global Underground Dave's 20's also saw tours to South America on numerous occasions including gigs at D-Edge in Sao Paolo and Infierno in Cordoba, Europe, China, even eastern Russia ...

Despite a diagnosis of stage 4 cancer 3 years ago Dave - now 33 - continues to DJ & perform live, selectively and preferably outdoors, around the world. Dave is a regular visitor to Japan, appearing 2 or 3 times a year at his own Mariana event where he commands a noisily enthusiastic following. Each visit over the last 2 years has also seen Dave bring his eclectic taste in ambient, house, tech house, bass music and techno to Japan and worldwide audiences via Dommune & its AV online channel. Working via his mini agency MYMTokyo has seen Dave & his guests tour to Okinawa, Tokushima, Fukuoka, Sapporo, Nagasaki, Osaka & Nagoya over the years. 

Dave is currently living in the UK focusing on music production & his other main interest Yoga. Dave's debut 12-inch release 'Barreleye' is a collaboration with Iori on TIME TO EXPRESS, described by one reviewer as 'mesmerising' with other reviews from the likes of Richard Brophy (DJ Mag) with support by Horizontal Ground's AnD, Chris Liebing, Laurent Garnier and Konrad Black among others. A collection of the 'Return To Center' tracks of which 'Barreleye' is one, was released as full length CD in 2012. The MARIANA record label is set to launch in spring/summer 2013 with the likes of Mike Parker, Stanislav Tokachev, Iori and of course Tr nch all penned in for releases. The Mariana event in Tokyo goes from strength to strength and is set to start a new chapter at Eleven in 2013.  

www.mymtokyo.com

The Tr nch DJ set represents the sound of MARIANA, a currently Japan-based deep techno event project. What's to say?  I make music.  I mean what I say in my my lyrics completely, and where I don't feel like I can convey my meaning in words, I hope that the guitar can carry it for me.  There isn't an angle per se.  Art is an imitation of life, and life is often filled with triumph and tragedy, victories and defeats.  In seeking to recreate these moments, sometimes we learn a lot about ourselves.  Music is my greatest teacher about life.  I hope that I am able to reflect some of that truth back through the imperfect lens of my own being both as a musician and as a person.

Nash Albert is a Georgian singer-songwriter and musician from Tbilisi, Georgia, currently living in Moscow, Russia.

He is known as leader and songwriter of the Moscow band Blast (Blast Unit Moscow) in the period 1996 to 2013. Blast was one of the brightest, most successful, unique alternative bands of the Russian rock-n-roll scene. NME called them Â«the godfathers of the Russian alternative sceneÂ». The most successful album of Blast was produced my Martin â€œYouthâ€ Glover in 2013 and released in 2014. It received a lot of attention from the UK & European music industry. After the break-up of Blast, Nash went solo in 2014. This journey brought him into the orbit of a new set of creative collaborators, from Ian McNabb to Tim Palmer. During 2019 Nash spent several months in the mountains of Georgia at SVAS studios working on new album with Nashâ€™s old friend and co-writer Ric Berie. At the same time Tim was mixing and layering parts in Texas. Writing never stopped and some songs evolved right in the studio out of thin air. Nash and the band deliberately ignored stylistic boundaries: art rock and prog rock of the 70s were combined with the vibes of Dylan, Bowie and The Beatlesâ€™ psychedelic Magical Mystery Tour. Performing it with all the power of the 90s alternative rock gave a fresh and unexpected result. Once the album was finished it was mastered by the mighty Bob Ludwig. Album YET will be released in january 2022 !
